commentTextItems.html: as easy as they come. Full toss sliding into the pads and he's flicked that imperiously into the square leg boundary. The series is now level at 2-2.

commentPostTextItems.html: 4.50pm Kevin O'Brien - take a bow. Wickets, then had to go off on 9 because of a hamstring injury. Came out to bat in a crisis and then led the way with a fine counter-attack to keep this series alive. Afghanistan's spinners switched off briefly and lost the plot in a 10-minute passage where O'Brien went berserk. Such was the ferocity of his onslaught that it more than made up for yet aother top order wobble. Credit also to Gary Wilson for playing the role of the accumulator.

Big question now is will Kevin O'Brien play the decider on Friday? Hamstring injuries can take a while to heal. He was clearly not comfortable running, and so decided maybe hitting out was the best strategy. Worked wonders today as it came at a time where it looked like Ireland were being schooled by the Afghanistan spinners. Two attacking hits forced them to alter their line and lengths. It went downhill from there on.

"It's all coming together now," says Ireland captain William Porterfield. "We knew today would be a low-scoring affair. Restricting them to 220 was a great effort. We'll assess who is fit. We've had a couple of forced chances. Hopefully we can pick from a full squad for the final game on Friday."

No surprises with the Player of the Match award. Kevin O'Brien . "It's the same hamstring injury, which doesn't look too good. We'll reassess in the next 12-24 hours to see how it goes. As a batting unit, we spoke of how we need one from the top six to be there till the end. That's how it worked out. Afghanistan are a good bowling team. We knew they weren't going to lie down when they scored just 219."

"Top order hasn't clicked, that's a concern for us," says Afghanistan captain Asghar Stanikzai. "The good thing is our lower order is coming up with important contributions. I think 220 was a defendable total."
pradipto: "This is a commendable effort from the Irish on a slow and low turner, kind of pitch they are not accustomed too. Kevin O'brien still has it in him."

dismissalText.commentary: Hashmatullah Shahidi b Mulder 23 (45b 3x4 0x6 50m) SR: 51.11

dismissalComment.html: this is simply sensational bowling. There's flight, and so he's drawn forward. But in the process, he fails to account for the turn. Goes for the drive, the ball beats the inside edge by sneaking through the gap and onto the stumps. A wicket any lespinner would be proud of. He looked compact for large parts but one major error of playing down the wrong line has cost him big. Afghanistan in trouble.

dismissalText.commentary: Gulbadin Naib lbw b Mulder 2 (9b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 22.22

dismissalComment.html: pitches and straightens and strikes the pad, Naib was confused whether to play or let it go, loud appeal and given.

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c Balbirnie b McBrine 35 (55b 5x4 0x6 85m) SR: 63.63

dismissalComment.html: tossed up and Stanikzai goes after it and hits it down the ground to long on and the fielder is waiting there to grab it, Balbirnie takes the catch.

headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rashid Khan lbw b McBrine 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: loud appeal first ball, strikes the pad as he looks to play it to the onside, plays down the wrong line. Afghanistan in deep trouble as they are 83 for the loss of 7 wickets.

dismissalText.commentary: Shafiqullah lbw b Mulder 42 (42b 8x4 0x6 28m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: lovely delivery and Shafiq is struck on the pad in line with the off stump as he moves back to a straight delivery, clever bowling.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi c Thompson b O'Brien 41 (64b 3x4 0x6 85m) SR: 64.06

dismissalComment.html: full toss hit in the air to deep backward square leg and taken by Thompson.

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Amir Hamza c †Wilson b Murtagh 7 (8b 0x4 1x6 15m) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: short ball and Hamza gets a faint edge to the keeper, after he looked to pull.

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce b Gulbadin Naib 24 (42b 3x4 0x6 57m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: through the gate. Naib pierces Joyce's defence. Straight ball, sticks the bat out, probably expecting it to angle away from him. Ends up leaving a gap between bat and pad. The ball sneaks through and disturbs the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling c Shafiqullah b Mohammad Nabi 28 (30b 4x4 1x6 38m) SR: 93.33

dismissalComment.html: chipped straight to mid-on. And it is a huge, huge blow for Ireland. Paul Stirling, the in-form batsman, gets off to a start and perishes. Comes down the track and the ball stops on him a little, as a result he ends up closing the bat face early and gets a leading edge

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield st †Mohammad Shahzad b Mohammad Nabi 6 (14b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: turn outside off and Shahzad reckons he has had him stumped. This has been referred to the third umpire. He was pushing forward and dragged the backfoot outside the crease as the ball beats the outside edge. He slides it back in but not before Shahzad whips off the bails in a flash. That wicket was as much the keeper's as much as it was the bowler's. Superb effort all-round

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie b Mohammad Nabi 22 (36b 2x4 0x6 52m) SR: 61.11

dismissalComment.html: this one keeps low and sneaks through his defence. The ball drifts in from wide of the crease, pitches on off and skids straight on. Balbirnie was looking to work it with the turn when there was none. Couldn't do much really as the ball didn't bounce enough. Bat didn't come down on time either. Big, big wicket. He was a split-second late on the shot as well.

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien not out 72 (60b 8x4 2x6 67m) SR: 120

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Nabi b Rashid Khan
dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson c Mohammad Nabi b Rashid Khan 41 (67b 3x4 0x6 96m) SR: 61.19

dismissalComment.html: holes out to the lone man at deep midwicket. Poor ball. It was too short, he could have played it wherever he pleased. This time, he hit it straight down the throat of the fielder. The ball may have skidded on a touch to prevent him from playing it behind square. Afghanistan are still alive.

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Thompson b Rashid Khan 8 (14b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: this time he's got his man. Foxed him completely in length. Thompson feels for the ball, I suspect he was expecting a googly and so pushed outside the line. There was a big gap between bat and pad. This ball spun back in to sneak through. Created the doubt and then finally nipped it in the bud. Skillful from Rashid. Ireland in trouble

dismissalText.commentary: Andy McBrine b Mohammad Nabi 5 (8b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: beauty! Once again foxed by the turn. Had no clue if this would spin away as he prodded forward half-heartedly and saw the ball drift-in, straighten and hit off stump. Played down the wrong line again. Fourth for Nabi. The series is fast slipping for the Irish.

milestones.description: Mohammad Nabi has become the top wicket-taker for AFG in ODIs with 84 wickets, going past Dawlat Zadran's 80
Mohammad Nabi has become the top scorer for AFG in ODIs with 1902 runs, going past Shahzad's 1887
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for AFG, going past Asghar Afghan's 5
Rahmat Shah has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for AFG, going past Rashid Khan's record

stories.seoTitle: Kevin O'Brien 72* helps Ireland draw level
stories.summary: Kevin O'Brien fought through a hamstring injury and launched a fine counter-attack to give Ireland a come-from-behind win that helped them level the series
